parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In addition, difficulty shifting gears can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission is difficult to shift from park gear
the transmission fails to engage gears
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Differential failure can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to accidents or loss of control. In severe cases, it can also cause the vehicle to stall or become stranded.
symptoms: The differential is destroyed
requiring complete replacement
unusual noises or vibrations from the differential
the vehicle loses traction or stability.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Leaks and Fuel Odor
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel leaks and lingering fuel odors can pose a significant fire hazard, compromise the vehicle's structural integrity, and affect the health and well-being of occupants.
symptoms: Fuel leaks into the vehicle's interior
strong fuel odor inside the vehicle
fuel gauge malfunctions
potential health issues due to fuel exposure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty fuel gauge can lead to inaccurate fuel level readings, causing drivers to run out of fuel unexpectedly, which can result in accidents, injuries, or strandings.
symptoms: Fuel gauge malfunctions
inaccurate fuel level readings
sudden loss of power
stalling
or engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The frequent failure of the air conditioning system can cause discomfort and distraction to the driver and passengers, potentially leading to accidents or decreased vehicle safety.
symptoms: The air conditioning system fails to cool
the air conditioning system blows warm air
the evaporator unit leaks refrigerant
the evaporator unit needs to be replaced frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the evaporator unit can cause the air conditioning system to malfunction, leading to discomfort and distraction to the driver and passengers, potentially affecting vehicle safety.
symptoms: The air conditioning system fails to cool
the air conditioning system blows warm air
the evaporator unit leaks refrigerant
the evaporator unit needs to be replaced frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Driver's Side Seat Belt Buckle
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning seat belt buckle can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident, as the driver may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The driver's side seat belt does not buckle
the seat belt latch does not engage
the seat belt cannot be securely fastened.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the starter relay can cause the vehicle to be unable to start, leaving the driver stranded and potentially causing inconvenience or safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle will not start
the starter motor does not engage
the ignition switch does not respond
the battery is drained
the dashboard lights or accessories may not function.
